abstract:
This SPSS template file supports data entry for the Evaluation of Daily Activity Questionnaire (EDAQ). The EDAQ variable names are standardised and ready coded. A number of commonly used demographic variables are also included.&#13;
A separate "SPSS EDAQ template total domains scores data file A Hammond v1 2016.sav" is also available for entering total domain and component scores. The two files can be merged if required. The suffix 1 denotes Test 1 / baseline data entry. The suffix denotes Test 2/ follow-up data.&#13;
The data entry files can be freely used and modified as required.&#13;
&#13;
The EDAQ User Manual v2 (2016) and the EDAQ are available from this site at: http://usir.salford.ac.uk/view/authors/10108.html#group&#13;
Look under “Monographs”&#13;
The manual explains how to: code the EDAQ in SPSS (or other statistical package); and score the EDAQ.
